<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1404,1430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 15.5–16.3; head length: 1.5–2.0; head width: 3.9–3.2; pronotal length: 3.0–3.2; pronotal width: 9.1–10.0; abdominal width: 8.5–8.7; scutellum length: 6.7–7.5; scutellum width: 5.4–5.6; length of antennal segments. I: 0.9–1.0; II: 2.0–3.4; III: 1.0–1.3; IV: 4.0–4.4; V: 4.5–5.7.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1512,1538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along half of its extension, remaining smoky black. Anterolateral margin with few dark punctures dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[935,1039,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
). Cicatrices with dark brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[501,606,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin concolorous (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1247,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with stripes dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[439,544,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 18H</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[746,873,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim shallowly excavated (
<figureCitation box="[159,252,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup small, reniform, ventral margin with a short medial digitiform projection, adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[718,842,1692,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). Head of the paramere broad; anterior lobe short and truncated; posterior lobe large and acuminated; stalk with a low ridge on inner face evanescent toward anterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[159,283,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral dense tufts of long setae separated by median wide glabrous area; posterior face barrel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[420,545,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4B–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with medial excavation in “V”, margin swollen; expansions large, broad, rounded, distally light yellow, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1332,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1188,2043]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1908,1934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Comments.</emphasis>
The number 8599/34 attached to the 
<typeStatus box="[754,850,1909,1935]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">paratype</typeStatus>
female deposited in the collection of MNHN means entry n° 8599 of the year 1834 on the catalogue d’Orbigny (1834) with the following information: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1277,1364,1944,1970]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Bolivie</collectingCountry>
, province 
<collectingRegion box="[205,469,1980,2006]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Santa Cruz de la Sierra</collectingRegion>
, punaise sur buissons et arbustes à la lisière de bois épais et humides, vole facilement sur plantes cultivées, 
<date box="[394,572,2016,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" value="1830-11">novembre 1830</date>
” [
<collectingCountry box="[596,684,2016,2042]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[696,1065,2016,2042]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Santa Cruz de la Sierra province</collectingRegion>
, bug on bushes and shrubs at the edge of thick, damp woods, flies easily on cultivated plants, 
<date box="[819,1005,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" value="1830-11">November 1830</date>
]. This species like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1212,1390,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1390,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,304,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[151,304,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the head of the paramere broad with posterior lobe well-developed and rounded to acuminated, anterior lobe somewhat developed and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[715,816,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">Figs. 4B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[831,880,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">16B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[894,945,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">13B</figureCitation>
). The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1111,1351,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassimarginatum">
<emphasis box="[1111,1351,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. crassimarginatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the other two by the anterior lobe of the paramere slightly developed (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1202,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) (more developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,331,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[151,331,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[385,540,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[385,540,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[555,668,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">Figs. 16B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[680,729,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">13B</figureCitation>
); and superior process of the genital cup curved ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) (almost straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[411,590,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[411,590,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[644,798,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[644,798,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="195" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,367,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the swollen margin of the median excavation of ventral rim of the pygophore (
<emphasis box="[161,245,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">crassus</emphasis>
= thick, stout).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
